rs_bp.register(app, bp_options) is called with url_prefix='/api' only — no '/users' component\",\n    \"Step 8: BlueprintSetupState for users_bp is created (line 321) with url_prefix='/api' (from options, line 72-74)\",\n    \"Step 9: add_url_rule() (line 98-102) prepends '/api' to all users_bp routes, yielding '/api/<route>' instead of '/api/users/<route>'\"\n  ],\n  \"trigger_conditions\": [\n    \"users_bp is created with url_prefix=None (not set at construction time) AND no url_prefix kwarg is passed to api_bp.register_blueprint(users_bp) — both sources of the child prefix are None, so the child prefix is silently omitted\",\n    \"users_bp.url_prefix is set (e.g. '/users') but api_bp.register_blueprint(users_bp, url_prefix=...) overrides it with a different value — the blueprint's own url_prefix is shadowed by the registration kwarg (line 364-365 only falls back when bp_options has no url_prefix key)\",\n    \"Deeply nested blueprints where an intermediate level has url_prefix=None and the registration call also omits url_prefix — the None propagates and breaks prefix concatenation for all descendants\",\n    \"The combination logic at lines 367-374 has no 'else' branch: when both state.url_prefix and bp_url_prefix are None, no 'url_prefix' key is added to bp_options, causing BlueprintSetupState to fall back to the child blueprint's url_prefix attribute (which may also be None)\"\n  ],\n  \"code_paths\": [\n    {\n      \"path\": \"src/flask/sansio/blueprints.py\",\n      \"description\": \"Primary file — BlueprintSetupState (prefix application) and Blueprint.register (nested prefix resolution logic)\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \"src/flask/sansio/app.py\",\n      \"description\": \"App.register_blueprint entry point — delegates directly to blueprint.register(self, options)\"\n    }\n  ],\n  \"ownership\": \"Blueprint registration subsystem — specifically the nested blueprint URL prefix resolution in Blueprint.register() and the prefix application in BlueprintSetupState.add_url_rule()\",\n  \"key_logic\": {\n    \"prefix_resolution_location\": \"src/flask/sansio/blueprints.py:349-377 (Blueprint.register, nested blueprints loop)\",\n    \"prefix_application_location\": \"src/flask/sansio/blueprints.py:98-102 (BlueprintSetupState.add_url_rule)\",\n    \"initial_prefix_extraction\": \"src/flask/sansio/blueprints.py:72-77 (BlueprintSetupState.__init__)\",\n    \"combination_logic\": \"If both state.url_prefix and bp_url_prefix are non-None: concatenate with '/'. If only one is non-None: use that one. If both are None: no url_prefix key is set in bp_options, child blueprint falls back to its own url_prefix attribute.\",\n    \"the_dropped_prefix_scenario\": \"api_bp.register_blueprint(users_bp) — no url_prefix kwarg. If users_bp.url_prefix is None, bp_url_prefix stays None. state.url_prefix='/api'. Branch at line 373 fires: bp_options['url_prefix'] = '/api'. Child prefix '/users' is never included.\"\n  },\n  \"severity\": {\n    \"level\": \"medium\",\n    \"rationale\": \"Silent data loss — routes are registered at the wrong URL path with no error or warning. The bug only manifests when the nested blueprint's url_prefix is None at construction time and not supplied as a kwarg to register_blueprint. Correct usage (supplying url_prefix at either construction or registration) works as expected. The failure mode is a missing URL segment, which typically causes 404s rather than security issues.\"\n  }\n}\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":112,"cache_read_input_tokens":23021,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":112},"output_tokens":25,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"37ea7f6a-f9fb-4b12-8b33-82ddaca1a24d","uuid":"dd70630d-2d52-479e-858f-fe51213bdc8f"}
