{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_019ZnNhTAQPYC7XnZ2ej4Khe","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Here's a summary of the findings:\n\n## Flask Nested Blueprint URL Prefix Resolution\n\n**Key file:** `src/flask/sansio/blueprints.py`\n\n### Where it happens\nThe nested blueprint URL prefix resolution is in `Blueprint.register()` at **lines 349–377**. The logic:\n\n```python\n# lines 364-374\nif bp_url_prefix is None:\n    bp_url_prefix = blueprint.url_prefix  # fallback to bp's own attribute\n\nif state.url_prefix is not None and bp_url_prefix is not None:\n    bp_options[\"url_prefix\"] = state.url_prefix.rstrip(\"/\") + \"/\" + bp_url_prefix.lstrip(\"/\")\nelif bp_url_prefix is not None:\n    bp_options[\"url_prefix\"] = bp_url_prefix\nelif state.url_prefix is not None:\n    bp_options[\"url_prefix\"] = state.url_prefix\n# ELSE: both None — no url_prefix set at all\n```\n\n### When the nested prefix is dropped\nThe bug fires when:\n1. `users_bp` is created with **no `url_prefix`** (i.e. `users_bp.url_prefix = None`)\n2. **AND** `api_bp.register_blueprint(users_bp)` is called with **no `url_prefix` kwarg**\n\nBoth sources of the child prefix are `None`, so `bp_url_prefix` stays `None`. The branch at line 373 fires, setting `url_prefix = state.url_prefix = \"/api\"` — the `/users` segment is silently lost.\n\n### Error chain\n`register_blueprint(users_bp)` → `bp_url_prefix = None` → fallback `blueprint.url_prefix = None` → only parent prefix `\"/api\"` survives → `BlueprintSetupState.add_url_rule()` (line 98–102) prepends only `\"/api\"` → routes land at `/api/<route>` instead of `/api/users/<route>`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1586,"cache_read_input_tokens":23133,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1586},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"37ea7f6a-f9fb-4b12-8b33-82ddaca1a24d","uuid":"fa6f3fd7-c631-46bc-bc02-18a36deeff80"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":95480,"duration_api_ms":95246,"num_turns":8,"result":"Here's a summary of the findings:\n\n## Flask Nested Blueprint URL Prefix Resolution\n\n**Key file:** `src/flask/sansio/blueprints.py`\n\n### Where it happens\nThe nested blueprint URL prefix resolution is in `Blueprint.register()` at **lines 349–377**. The logic:\n\n```python\n# lines 364-374\nif bp_url_prefix is None:\n    bp_url_prefix = blueprint.url_prefix  # fallback to bp's own attribute\n\nif state.url_prefix is not None and bp_url_prefix is not None:\n    bp_options[\"url_prefix\"] = state.url_prefix.rstrip(\"/\") + \"/\" + bp_url_prefix.lstrip(\"/\")\nelif bp_url_prefix is not None:\n    bp_options[\"url_prefix\"] = bp_url_prefix\nelif state.url_prefix is not None:\n    bp_options[\"url_prefix\"] = state.url_prefix\n# ELSE: both None — no url_prefix set at all\n```\n\n### When the nested prefix is dropped\nThe bug fires when:\n1. `users_bp` is created with **no `url_prefix`** (i.e. `users_bp.url_prefix = None`)\n2. **AND** `api_bp.register_blueprint(users_bp)` is called with **no `url_prefix` kwarg**\n\nBoth sources of the child prefix are `None`, so `bp_url_prefix` stays `None`. The branch at line 373 fires, setting `url_prefix = state.url_prefix = \"/api\"` — the `/users` segment is silently lost.\n\n### Error chain\n`register_blueprint(users_bp)` → `bp_url_prefix = None` → fallback `blueprint.url_prefix = None` → only parent prefix `\"/api\"` survives → `BlueprintSetupState.add_url_rule()` (line 98–102) prepends only `\"/api\"` → routes land at `/api/<route>` instead of `/api/users/<route>`.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"37ea7f6a-f9fb-4b12-8b33-82ddaca1a24d","total_cost_usd":0.2999989,"usage":{"input_tokens":9,"cache_creation_input_tokens":17622,"cache_read_input_tokens":152223,"output_tokens":2981,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_in